	('557fdfc6-2184-4043-a801-7a8cac1f2fc5','CREATE','Project','29','{\"Project\":{\"id\":\"29\",\"owner_user_id\":\"2\",\"status_id\":\"6\",\"likelihood_id\":\"2\",\"programme_id\":\"2\",\"title\":\"Business Advocacy for Peace (CP)\",\"fund_code\":\"ER05LR\",\"summary\":\"BAP will continue to work towards these outcomes\\/outputs: 1) Greater evidence base and improved understanding on the inter-linkages between economic cooperation and conflict\\/peace\\u2014outputs: 2 reports (on economic & conflict analysis of selected case studies and on economic peace dividends of regional cooperation), an analysis of inter-linkages between economic frameworks (EU, WTO, etc) and conflict\\/peace. 2) New models and frameworks for cooperation\\u2014outputs: policy recommendations, policy dialogues on the trans-Ingur\\/I process, research and advocacy meetings. 3) Greater capacity and engagement by economic actors to be agents for change locally and regionally\\u2014outputs: an expert-advocacy network consolidated and engaged in policy dialogue with national and international policy makers; piloting of cross-divide economic initiatives.\\r\\n\\r\\nBAP activities for 2013-15 include: In Strand 1 (Regional research on the linkages between regional economic cooperation and peace): Regional research meetings, Desk\\/ field research, Publication of research reports, Policy dialogues in the region and Europe. In Strand 2 (Regulatory framework for trans-Ingur\\/i economic cooperation): Discuss research findings (on shadow economy relations & legal analysis) with stakeholders\\/ authorities in Tbilisi, Sukhumi, Europe (EU, WTO), Expert meetings to develop actionable recommendations for regulating cross-divide economic relations; Dialogue meetings with regional policy-makers. In Strand 3 (Greater capacity & engagement of economic actors): Promote policy-practice\",\"start_date\":null,\"finish_date\":null,\"value_required\":\"359988\",\"value_sourced\":\"0\",\"created\":\"2015-06-16 09:35:18\"