	('5580003c-6bf4-4af8-a61c-23c1ac1f2fc5','READ','Project','34','{\"Project\":{\"id\":\"34\",\"owner_user_id\":\"3\",\"status_id\":\"5\",\"likelihood_id\":\"2\",\"programme_id\":\"2\",\"title\":\"UN Women IAGE project\",\"fund_code\":\"ER02RR\",\"summary\":\"Four sub-projects address a common problem (articulated by the participants at the seminar): \\u201ctraditional\\u201d and narrow narratives on gender create negative consequences, ranging from increased school and domestic violence to disenfranchisement and lack of participation in civil and social life. The solutions to the problems identified are specific, but all utilise various activities to challenge stereotypes and stimulate discussion to expand awareness of the role of women beyond the domestic or sexualised stereotype. 1) Gender and Peace through the eyes of teenagers - Beneficiaries: approx. 75 teenagers from 6 schools aged 14-18 and their family members from areas affected by conflict; the wider community in Shida Kartli (through media interventions). 2) Psycho-social support to women war veterans. - Beneficiaries: At least 30 participants of round table; 200+ recipients of the publication; at least 50 attendees of the presentation; the wider public through media coverage. 3) Changing the status of Ossetian women. - Beneficiaries: target 1000+ visitors to the social media web pages; focus group participants. 4) Fotoreal \\u2013 overcoming gender stereotypes and raising profile of women. -  Beneficiaries: 50 youth age 16-25; 100+ visitors to photo exhibition 5) Common activity \",\"start_date\":null,\"finish_date\":null,\"value_required\":\"22600\",\"value_sourced\":\"22600\",\"created\":\"2015-06-16 11:53:48\",\"modified\":\"2015-06-16 11:53:48\",\"deleted\":false},\"Status\":{\"id\":\"5\",\"name\":\"Contracted\",\"short_name\":\"contracted\",\"sort_order\":\"3\"},\"Likelihood\":{\"id\":\"2\",\"name\":\"Confirmed\",\"short_name\":\"confirmed\",\"sort_order\":\"4\"},\"Programme\":{\"id\":\"2\",\"name\":